32
00:01:26.750 --> 00:01:28.580
An engine was destroyed.

33
00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:31.250
All of this on your watch.

34
00:01:32.460 --> 00:01:35.120
What happens in the dirt
has to stand up on the carpet.

35
00:01:35.220 --> 00:01:37.630
Right here. in this office.

36
00:01:39.900 --> 00:01:42.970
It's a really nice office.

37
00:01:44.970 --> 00:01:47.300
Not bad for a kid
from Edgewater.

38
00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:49.100
Thank you.

39
00:01:51.810 --> 00:01:55.280
So. obviously. the department
has some questions

40
00:01:55.380 --> 00:01:57.180
about that incident. Chief.

41
00:02:01.950 --> 00:02:03.890
Ask away.

42
00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:06.290
Okay. I'll start simple.

43
00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:07.990
How'd you get the shiner?

44
00:02:08.820 --> 00:02:11.390
That's what you want
to start with?

45
00:02:11.460 --> 00:02:13.260
Happened on the incident.
didn't it?

46
00:02:13.330 --> 00:02:15.060
Yes.

47
00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:16.670
Well. then it's relevant.

48
00:02:18.300 --> 00:02:19.700
It was...

49
00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:23.970
a stressful call.

50
00:02:24.070 --> 00:02:26.880
Had two counties on the line.

51
00:02:28.410 --> 00:02:30.180
Let's just say that
tempers ran hot.

52
00:02:30.310 --> 00:02:33.420
Captain Crawford. I.C.
Can you hear me?

53
00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:36.150
I repeat.
I need an acknowledgment. Over.

54
00:02:36.250 --> 00:02:38.520
Captain Crawford.
can you hear me?

55
00:02:38.650 --> 00:02:40.820
Perez. did you just
lose my engine?

56
00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:42.860
Get out of my face
and let me work.

57
00:02:42.990 --> 00:02:44.930
Did Bode surface on the radio?

58
00:02:47.060 --> 00:02:50.100
- Come on. This is Bode you sent out there to freelance.
- To save a kid

59
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.870
- who never should've been out there in the first place. Chief.
- No. no. it's on you.

60
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.900
You're the I.C.
It's your incident.

61
00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:56.340
I know that. Chief.

62
00:02:57.110 --> 00:03:00.240
You just lost radio contact
with four firefighters.

63
00:03:00.340 --> 00:03:03.880
this thing is raging harder
than it was nine hours ago.

64
00:03:04.010 --> 00:03:07.720
and you're counting
on a rookies' line to hold?

65
00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:09.890
What kind of ass-backward
incident are you running?

66
00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:12.150
- Shut up. I can't hear.
- Lookout One. I.C.

67
00:03:12.260 --> 00:03:13.790
Do you copy?

68
00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:15.420
How do you copy?

69
00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:18.030
Where are you guys?
Can you hear me? Over.

70
00:03:21.830 --> 00:03:25.200
Lookout One.
I repeat. do you hear me?

71
00:03:25.300 --> 00:03:27.370
Over. Jake.

72
00:03:29.540 --> 00:03:31.840
Lookout One. I.C.
How do you copy?

73
00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:34.040
Can you hear me?
Where are you guys?

74
00:03:35.540 --> 00:03:38.110
M-Malcolm. Malcolm!

75
00:03:39.550 --> 00:03:41.380
Keep it up. fellas. Keep going!

76
00:03:41.520 --> 00:03:43.920
You guys are cutting line
like seasoned firefighters.

77
00:03:44.020 --> 00:03:46.690
Every slash in the dirt
is one step closer.

78
00:03:46.790 --> 00:03:47.690
Keep going.

79
00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:49.590
You about to pass out like me?

80
00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:51.360
Trying not to think about it.

81
00:03:51.460 --> 00:03:52.930
Eve.

82
00:03:53.060 --> 00:03:54.230
You got eyes on Jake?

83
00:03:54.330 --> 00:03:57.070
Uh. sorry. Chief.
that's a negative.

84
00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:00.740
All right.
what's Three Rock's status?

85
00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:03.340
We are still cutting line
to Sage Knoll.

86
00:04:03.440 --> 00:04:06.240
Keep 'em going. And keep hoping
that these southeast winds

87
00:04:06.380 --> 00:04:07.610
don't kick up any more.

88
00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:09.080
Okay. well. what are they at?

89
00:04:09.210 --> 00:04:11.050
Fifteen. 16 miles an hour.

90
00:04:11.150 --> 00:04:12.920
Any more than that
and we're in big trouble.

91
00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:16.220
It's the last defense
keeping fire out of Edgewater.

92
00:04:16.320 --> 00:04:17.850
Your line has to hold.

93
00:04:18.790 --> 00:04:19.790
Copy that.

94
00:04:19.890 --> 00:04:22.560
Copy that.

95
00:04:22.660 --> 00:04:25.290
All right. guys.
keep moving. keep going!

96
00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:28.300
I know you're tired. Let's go!

97
00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:35.140
- Bode. do you copy?
- I'm sorry. Chief.

98
00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:37.440
This was supposed to be
a simple pickup.

99
00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:39.310
And based on the information
that I had at the time.

100
00:04:39.440 --> 00:04:41.440
it was supposed
to be safe and easy.

101
00:04:41.540 --> 00:04:44.110
Yeah. but now it's been five
minutes with no communication.

102
00:04:44.250 --> 00:04:46.820
so come on.
what is your plan. I.C.?

103
00:04:49.750 --> 00:04:51.950
Where in the hell is Tyler?

104
00:04:52.050 --> 00:04:54.960
- Oh. God.
- Sharon? Sharon?

105
00:04:55.090 --> 00:04:56.660
Where's my son?

106
00:04:57.630 --> 00:04:58.960
Somebody tell me.

107
00:04:59.060 --> 00:05:00.500
H-How'd you get in here?

108
00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:02.630
Sheriff's escort.
Now can you answer my question?

109
00:05:02.730 --> 00:05:05.170
Where is my son? Where is he?

110
00:05:05.270 --> 00:05:07.600
How was I supposed
to answer that question?

111
00:05:07.700 --> 00:05:11.140
I had two mothers asking me
where the hell their sons are

112
00:05:11.240 --> 00:05:13.010
while I'm handling
a two-county incident.

113
00:05:13.140 --> 00:05:15.410
So. how did you answer
that question?

114
00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:18.880
I told the truth.

115
00:05:23.020 --> 00:05:24.250
Where is he?

116
00:05:24.350 --> 00:05:26.190
I don't know.

117
00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:30.160
Keep breathing.

118
00:05:51.350 --> 00:05:53.750
So. uh. let me see
if I have this straight.

119
00:05:53.820 --> 00:05:58.290
As I.C.. you lost track
of Jake and Malcolm Crawford

120
00:05:58.350 --> 00:06:01.860
and Engineer Erickson.
and separately.

121
00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:03.830
Leone and a civilian?

122
00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:07.360
Wh... What was
going through your head. man?

123
00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:10.930
Any scenario in which
they didn't turn up dead.

124
00:06:24.010 --> 00:06:27.220
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

125
00:06:28.150 --> 00:06:30.350
We're alive? We're alive?

126
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:36.830
Bode?

127
00:06:36.930 --> 00:06:38.860
- Bode?
- Over here.

128
00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:50.840
What the hell?

129
00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:52.710
- What the hell?
- You got to-you got to bring down your body temp.

130
00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:55.210
It's hot.
It's hot. it's burning...

131
00:06:55.310 --> 00:06:57.050
The moisture will still help
lower it. Doesn't matter.

132
00:06:57.150 --> 00:06:59.410
Here. pour that down your neck.

133
00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:06.050
I.C.. this is
Firefighter Leone.

134
00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:07.490
I've got Tyler here with me.

135
00:07:07.590 --> 00:07:09.220
Yes.

136
00:07:09.360 --> 00:07:11.830
I deployed a fire shelter near
the Ferndale Ranger Station.

137
00:07:11.930 --> 00:07:14.160
- Both of us are uninjured.
- Copy. Leone.

138
00:07:14.260 --> 00:07:16.030
Wait. t-this is good. right?
They're-they're safe?

139
00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:17.730
This is good.

140
00:07:22.540 --> 00:07:24.840
Our egress is blocked
due to active fire on Route 38.

141
00:07:24.910 --> 00:07:26.370
No. Oh...

142
00:07:26.480 --> 00:07:28.410
- Okay.
- What does that mean?

143
00:07:28.540 --> 00:07:30.850
Chloe MacKenzie should never
have been in that command tent.

144
00:07:30.910 --> 00:07:32.920
Tyler never should never
have been at that fire.

145
00:07:33.020 --> 00:07:34.420
He snuck into my truck. Chief.

146
00:07:34.520 --> 00:07:37.050
Well. maybe you got distracted
by your pre-deploy.

147
00:07:37.150 --> 00:07:39.450
Distracted?
I was on point. prepared.

148
00:07:39.590 --> 00:07:41.590
I was cautious.
And it's a good thing I was...

149
00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:43.290
What? What's a good thing?

150
00:07:43.390 --> 00:07:45.590
That you were in charge
of the entire County Line Fire?

151
00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:47.300
Hmm?

152
00:07:47.430 --> 00:07:49.770
You still think
that was a good idea?

153
00:07:49.900 --> 00:07:51.800
Chief.

154
00:07:52.740 --> 00:07:56.470
No B.C. ever wants a loss
of life on an incident. ever.

155
00:07:57.240 --> 00:07:58.810
- What does that mean?
- I-It means that

156
00:07:58.910 --> 00:08:00.380
we made radio contact with them.

157
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.780
and. uh. we're gonna
get them out. all right?

158
00:08:02.880 --> 00:08:04.580
What-what happens
in this scenario. right now?

159
00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:07.380
This is...
We're gonna figure it out now.

160
00:08:07.480 --> 00:08:09.650
What does-what does
"figure it out" mean?

161
00:08:09.790 --> 00:08:11.390
How do you figure... What does
it mean. "figuring it out"?

162
00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:13.060
It means that we don't have
a lot of time to sit here

163
00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:14.890
and answer all these questions
for you. all right?

164
00:08:14.960 --> 00:08:16.790
Sharon. can you please get her
out of here so that I can focus

165
00:08:16.930 --> 00:08:18.430
- on strategizing...
- No. no. You're not kicking me out.

166
00:08:18.490 --> 00:08:20.430
No. you cannot kick me out.
I am his mother.

167
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:22.030
- With all due respect. I-I...
- No. no. I'm gonna report your ass

168
00:08:22.130 --> 00:08:23.200
- to Cal Fire so fast.
- You need... I-I need

169
00:08:23.300 --> 00:08:25.770
some space to work! Please.

170
00:08:25.870 --> 00:08:27.300
Thank you.

171
00:08:27.400 --> 00:08:29.470
How are you so calm about this?

172
00:08:29.570 --> 00:08:31.370
'Cause I trust Manny.

173
00:08:32.780 --> 00:08:35.740
All right. Bode Coyote.
let's get your ass out of there.

174
00:08:36.580 --> 00:08:38.850
Hey. How the hell
are we gonna get out of here?

175
00:08:38.980 --> 00:08:40.250
Manny will rescue us.

176
00:08:40.320 --> 00:08:41.780
What... Wait. what if
they don't come in time?

177
00:08:41.880 --> 00:08:43.820
Listen to me. Some of
the toughest firefighters

178
00:08:43.920 --> 00:08:46.090
never go through
what you just did.

179
00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:49.190
But you made it.
Don't give up now.

180
00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:51.690
Stay close.

181
00:08:56.730 --> 00:08:59.330
I.C.. I've got eyes
on a downed engine.

182
00:08:59.430 --> 00:09:01.800
Possible rollover.
crew status is unknown.

183
00:09:01.870 --> 00:09:03.210
Awaiting instructions.

184
00:09:03.310 --> 00:09:04.670
You see a number on that rig?

185
00:09:04.770 --> 00:09:06.710
3084. Drake County.

186
00:09:06.840 --> 00:09:08.710
Whoever's inside there just
went for one hell of a tumble

187
00:09:08.810 --> 00:09:10.550
down the south-facing ravine.

188
00:09:11.350 --> 00:09:12.620
It's Jake. Jake's in there.

189
00:09:12.680 --> 00:09:14.020
I want you to look around
for me.

190
00:09:14.150 --> 00:09:15.350
What do you see?

191
00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:17.250
Is there anyone
outside that vehicle?

192
00:09:19.190 --> 00:09:21.090
Negative.

193
00:09:23.690 --> 00:09:24.690
All right. Bode.

194
00:09:24.790 --> 00:09:26.730
With Route 38 scorched.

195
00:09:26.830 --> 00:09:28.400
it looks like the best way out

196
00:09:28.530 --> 00:09:30.630
runs straight through
that south-facing ravine.

197
00:09:30.700 --> 00:09:33.340
I'm gonna send. uh. I'm gonna
send a rescue there for you two

198
00:09:33.400 --> 00:09:35.240
and for that engine crew.
Can you link up with them?

199
00:09:35.370 --> 00:09:37.870
Copy. I.C. Already on the move.

200
00:09:39.910 --> 00:09:42.410
That's it?
That-that's the whole story?

201
00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:45.850
Hmm.

202
00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:48.820
When an incident
goes this far sideways.

203
00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:52.620
it is the department's
responsibility to learn from it.

204
00:09:52.720 --> 00:09:54.260
for future safety.

205
00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:55.820
That's my only
agenda here. Manny.

206
00:09:55.890 --> 00:09:57.190
I am on your side.

207
00:09:57.290 --> 00:09:59.030
You're on my side.

208
00:09:59.130 --> 00:10:00.560
- Yeah.
- Can I ask you something?

209
00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:01.960
Shoot.

210
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:04.400
Why'd the brass choose you
to do this hot wash?

211
00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:07.040
It comes with
the assistant unit chief title.

212
00:10:07.100 --> 00:10:09.910
No. no. no. come on.
There's. like. what...

213
00:10:10.010 --> 00:10:12.410
at least a dozen other AUCs
in the Northern Region?

214
00:10:12.510 --> 00:10:14.040
They could've done it. Why you?

215
00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:17.180
I suppose you'd have to ask
the fire chief that one.

216
00:10:17.910 --> 00:10:21.520
I have a guess. actually.
if-if you're cool with it.

217
00:10:21.580 --> 00:10:23.620
Knock yourself out.

218
00:10:23.720 --> 00:10:25.520
I think that you're
a friend of 42's.

219
00:10:25.620 --> 00:10:27.220
and you're playing good cop.
and you're just hoping...

220
00:10:27.290 --> 00:10:28.690
you're hoping
and hoping and hoping...

221
00:10:28.760 --> 00:10:30.560
that I'm gonna lower my defense.

222
00:10:30.660 --> 00:10:33.330
spill somebody's
dirty laundry. right?

223
00:10:33.430 --> 00:10:34.800
Right?

224
00:10:37.570 --> 00:10:39.370
Let me ask you a question.

225
00:10:40.100 --> 00:10:44.370
Why did you send
a teenage civilian and my nephew

226
00:10:44.470 --> 00:10:47.610
to a crashed Drake County rig
in the middle of a wildfire?

227
00:10:47.740 --> 00:10:48.880
I did my due diligence.

228
00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:50.610
I checked the maps.
I radioed units.

229
00:10:50.710 --> 00:10:52.580
That fire was blocking
the path back to us.

230
00:10:52.680 --> 00:10:54.380
Okay. so. then. why not just
tell them to stay put?

231
00:10:54.450 --> 00:10:56.120
Because the area
was a dirty burn. Chief.

232
00:10:56.220 --> 00:10:58.250
There were embers everywhere.

233
00:10:58.320 --> 00:11:01.560
That crashed rig was the safest
place for Bode and Tyler.

234
00:11:11.600 --> 00:11:13.400
We got to get out of this cab.

235
00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:16.810
My radio.
Where the hell is it?

236
00:11:23.350 --> 00:11:27.180
I'm gonna cut myself free.
then I'm gonna cut you.

237
00:11:39.160 --> 00:11:40.860
All right.

238
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:44.030
Hang on. I'm coming.

239
00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:50.540
Let me see you.

240
00:11:51.310 --> 00:11:53.380
Hold on. you-you're bleeding.

241
00:11:55.180 --> 00:11:57.510
This is not my blood. I'm good.

242
00:11:57.610 --> 00:12:00.880
- Ringo.
- His pulse is rapid.

243
00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:03.550
All right.

244
00:12:05.550 --> 00:12:09.120
Just hang on.
Okay.

245
00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:12.360
You copy. I.C.?

246
00:12:12.460 --> 00:12:14.460
This is Jake Crawford.

247
00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:15.860
Do you copy?

248
00:12:15.960 --> 00:12:17.400
All right. copy.

249
00:12:17.530 --> 00:12:18.870
It's good to hear
your voice. brother.

250
00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:21.500
- What's your sitrep?
- Well...

251
00:12:21.570 --> 00:12:24.240
rocks on Route 38

252
00:12:24.340 --> 00:12:26.110
forced our engine to tumble over

253
00:12:26.210 --> 00:12:28.210
off of a slope.

254
00:12:29.910 --> 00:12:31.810
We took out
a couple of power lines

255
00:12:31.910 --> 00:12:34.450
and two of us
are banged up. but...

256
00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:37.150
our driver. he. uh...

257
00:12:37.220 --> 00:12:40.990
His name
is Engineer Ringo Erickson.

258
00:12:41.090 --> 00:12:43.490
Critical condition.
Get a rescue team here now.

259
00:12:43.560 --> 00:12:45.690
- Do you copy?
- I copy.

260
00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:47.000
Administer life support.

261
00:12:47.060 --> 00:12:48.930
Firefighter Leone's en route
with a civilian.

262
00:12:49.030 --> 00:12:50.270
Leone will assist with care.

263
00:12:50.370 --> 00:12:52.230
We're gonna get you guys
out of there.

264
00:12:52.330 --> 00:12:53.870
Yeah. okay. copy. I.C..

265
00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:56.440
but why is Leone
coming with a civilian?

266
00:12:56.540 --> 00:12:58.370
He got caught out there. too.

267
00:12:59.240 --> 00:13:01.210
Sit tight.

268
00:13:02.310 --> 00:13:05.450
All right. Option one.

269
00:13:08.420 --> 00:13:10.690
We wrap around
the flank of this fire

270
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:13.160
right here near Bailey Cliffs.

271
00:13:13.260 --> 00:13:15.560
And we send a small crew up.

272
00:13:15.620 --> 00:13:16.890
I'm waiting for the "but."

273
00:13:16.990 --> 00:13:19.900
Steep. rocky terrain
with big drop-offs.

274
00:13:19.960 --> 00:13:21.630
- But if we have a REMS team...
- We don't.

275
00:13:21.730 --> 00:13:24.030
And we're never getting
a spine board through all this.

276
00:13:24.130 --> 00:13:25.300
So. next option.

277
00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:26.900
All right. option two:
we anchor engines

278
00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:30.470
here at the flank.
and we lay some hose.

279
00:13:30.570 --> 00:13:32.570
Then it's a direct fire attack
to get to them.

280
00:13:32.670 --> 00:13:36.240
So. trees and terrain. with.
like. a thousand-foot hose lay.

281
00:13:36.340 --> 00:13:37.810
and-and our-our resources

282
00:13:37.910 --> 00:13:39.580
are already strapped thin
because we're trying to cover

283
00:13:39.650 --> 00:13:41.150
- that line that Three Rock cut.
- Chief.

284
00:13:41.280 --> 00:13:42.720
Chief. I'm just looking
for some solutions here.

285
00:13:42.820 --> 00:13:44.050
not problems. all right?

286
00:13:44.150 --> 00:13:45.620
I'm looking for an I.C.
that has a plan

287
00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:47.790
that doesn't include
burning down all of Edgewater

288
00:13:47.890 --> 00:13:50.490
- or leaving my son stranded.
- All right. all right. all right. I get it.

289
00:13:51.660 --> 00:13:53.830
Look. I've assessed
all the risk. all right?

290
00:13:53.930 --> 00:13:55.560
What-what if we pull the engines

291
00:13:55.630 --> 00:13:57.470
off the line
that Three Rock cut.

292
00:13:57.570 --> 00:13:59.430
and send them
to the engine crash?

293
00:13:59.500 --> 00:14:00.970
You want to leave
Three Rock unprotected?

294
00:14:01.100 --> 00:14:03.010
Nope. I want to rely
on the work they're doing

295
00:14:03.140 --> 00:14:04.170
to protect themselves.

296
00:14:04.310 --> 00:14:06.370
And all of Edgewater.

297
00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:08.310
One. two!

298
00:14:08.410 --> 00:14:11.350
- Three Rock!
- Let's go. baby.

299
00:14:16.950 --> 00:14:19.250
That's it. Cap. We're done.

300
00:14:19.350 --> 00:14:21.460
Hey. gentlemen.

301
00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:23.530
She's a beaut. y'all.

302
00:14:23.630 --> 00:14:25.430
Well done. Well done.

303
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:27.560
Captain Edwards.

304
00:14:27.660 --> 00:14:29.760
- You read me?
- Yeah. I'm here. Chief.

305
00:14:29.830 --> 00:14:31.930
Listen. we got
a low-pressure system

306
00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:33.570
heading southeast
towards Edgewater.

307
00:14:33.670 --> 00:14:36.800
and I hate to say it.
but these winds are picking up.

308
00:14:36.870 --> 00:14:38.510
Chief. my guys
just finished the line.

309
00:14:38.610 --> 00:14:41.040
I know. but now
you got to get it to 24 feet.

310
00:14:41.180 --> 00:14:43.310
Here's the good news. though.

311
00:14:43.410 --> 00:14:44.880
We found Bode and Jake.

312
00:14:44.980 --> 00:14:47.120
- Yeah? That's what I want to hear.
- Also.

313
00:14:47.180 --> 00:14:48.750
I'm pulling your engine support.

314
00:14:48.850 --> 00:14:50.390
rerouting it to rescue them.

315
00:14:50.520 --> 00:14:52.150
Wait. so you're gonna
have us do triple the work

316
00:14:52.220 --> 00:14:53.890
and pull our support?

317
00:14:54.020 --> 00:14:56.120
A brand-new hand crew. yeah?

318
00:14:56.220 --> 00:14:58.830
Barely any experience.
Baby firefighters.

319
00:14:58.890 --> 00:15:00.900
But somehow. you were convinced
that they could keep going?

320
00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:02.760
It wasn't about being convinced.

321
00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:04.530
It was about knowing
what needed to be done.

322
00:15:04.630 --> 00:15:06.070
Well. according to you.

323
00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:09.200
That's a mighty big wager
on a lot of inexperience.

324
00:15:09.300 --> 00:15:11.840
I believed in Eve.

325
00:15:11.940 --> 00:15:14.580
You and those boys
can pull this off.

326
00:15:14.710 --> 00:15:16.740
I know you can. Cap.

327
00:15:19.810 --> 00:15:20.980
Hey. gentlemen.

328
00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:23.120
I just watched you guys
move a mountain.

329
00:15:23.220 --> 00:15:25.920
and I hate to ask this of you...

330
00:15:27.060 --> 00:15:28.760
but now

331
00:15:28.890 --> 00:15:30.560
we got more work to do. okay?

332
00:15:30.690 --> 00:15:33.200
I need triple the width.
It's chief's orders.

333
00:15:33.300 --> 00:15:34.900
- Let's get to work.
- Come on. let's get a move on!

334
00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.030
- One. two...
- Three Rock!

335
00:15:37.130 --> 00:15:40.400
- Pick of your McLeods.
- We got it. Come on.

336
00:15:48.940 --> 00:15:50.310
- All right. Malcolm?
- Yeah.

337
00:15:50.410 --> 00:15:52.110
Look. we get him to the ground.
then assess

338
00:15:52.250 --> 00:15:54.220
and treat him first.
ASAP.

339
00:15:54.280 --> 00:15:56.750
All right. All right.

340
00:15:56.850 --> 00:15:57.790
- All right.
- Let me get his legs.

341
00:15:57.920 --> 00:15:59.020
Yep. All right. ready?

342
00:16:00.460 --> 00:16:02.560
- Got him?
- Yeah. I got him. Let him go.

343
00:16:02.620 --> 00:16:04.790
- All right. give me a second.
- Hold. hold.

344
00:16:04.890 --> 00:16:06.360
- All right. I got him.
- Yep.

345
00:16:06.430 --> 00:16:08.000
Let's go.

346
00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:16.140
Right behind you.

347
00:16:18.140 --> 00:16:20.080
I've never been happier
to see you. B.

348
00:16:20.140 --> 00:16:21.280
Is that guy dead?

349
00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:22.710
No. not if we can help it.

350
00:16:22.780 --> 00:16:24.610
What the hell is a kid
doing with you out here?

351
00:16:24.750 --> 00:16:26.310
Surviving a burnover
and hiking here with me

352
00:16:26.450 --> 00:16:27.750
to get this job done.

353
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:29.150
Who the hell is this?

354
00:16:29.280 --> 00:16:31.190
Malcolm. My brother.

355
00:16:33.790 --> 00:16:35.120
Tyler. help me look
for the rig's spine board.

356
00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:37.690
All right. airway's clear.

357
00:16:37.790 --> 00:16:39.260
pulse still rapid.

358
00:16:39.330 --> 00:16:41.200
But this head wound?
Look. we need gauze.

359
00:16:41.300 --> 00:16:42.730
Do you see any?

360
00:16:46.600 --> 00:16:48.670
Nope.

361
00:16:48.770 --> 00:16:51.640
Packs must have got tossed
when we came down the mountain.

362
00:16:51.740 --> 00:16:53.980
Oh. okay. give me that buff.

363
00:16:57.150 --> 00:16:58.480
Is he gonna be okay?

364
00:16:58.580 --> 00:17:00.750
This will do
until they get us out of here.

365
00:17:00.850 --> 00:17:02.850
Ready? Roll.

366
00:17:10.690 --> 00:17:12.930
Whoa. Bode.

367
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.860
Gonna get you out of here. okay?

368
00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:26.770
I.C.. this is Firefighter Leone.

369
00:17:26.870 --> 00:17:28.040
We've linked up
with Jake's engine crew.

370
00:17:28.180 --> 00:17:29.710
We got fire here now.

371
00:17:29.810 --> 00:17:31.880
Our only egress is through
some dangerous rocky terrain.

372
00:17:32.010 --> 00:17:33.950
Can't manage it
with a patient on a spine board.

373
00:17:34.050 --> 00:17:36.220
- Where are those engines?
- Copy. firefighter.

374
00:17:37.020 --> 00:17:40.460
Engine 1594. I.C. requesting
your ETA to that crashed rig.

375
00:17:40.520 --> 00:17:42.390
I.C.. Engine 1594.

376
00:17:42.490 --> 00:17:45.330
Fire blocked the access road.
Need rerouting.

377
00:17:45.390 --> 00:17:46.730
- No. This cannot be happening.
- Damn it.

378
00:17:46.830 --> 00:17:48.300
I'm calling for a water drop.

379
00:17:48.400 --> 00:17:50.330
Wait. what? No. no. no.
Chief. the winds. Come on.

380
00:17:50.430 --> 00:17:52.070
- I don't care!
- There's no way they're gonna put her up in the air.

381
00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:53.900
Engines hit significant delays.

382
00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:56.200
D.C. Leone's
ordering a water drop.

383
00:17:56.300 --> 00:17:57.870
We don't have time
to wait for a water drop.

384
00:17:58.010 --> 00:17:59.170
We got to do something.

385
00:17:59.270 --> 00:18:00.510
Yeah. well.

386
00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:01.880
engines and a water drop
are headed your way.

387
00:18:01.980 --> 00:18:03.040
You're just gonna have to wait

388
00:18:03.180 --> 00:18:04.210
and hang out
till they get there.

389
00:18:04.350 --> 00:18:05.950
B. are they close?

390
00:18:06.050 --> 00:18:08.080
I.C.. we can't wait.

391
00:18:08.220 --> 00:18:10.450
We got 500 gallons right here.

392
00:18:11.750 --> 00:18:14.320
You think you can punch
an egress hole?

393
00:18:14.390 --> 00:18:15.460
Do it.

394
00:18:15.560 --> 00:18:17.160
- Say yes.
- Worth a shot

395
00:18:17.230 --> 00:18:18.730
- with the deck gun. yeah.
- Chief. come on.

396
00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:21.060
- That's a great idea.
- Firefighter Leone.

397
00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:22.760
this is your division chief.

398
00:18:22.860 --> 00:18:24.430
You will deplete
your water supplies

399
00:18:24.570 --> 00:18:27.570
in 30 seconds and have
absolutely no defense.

400
00:18:27.670 --> 00:18:29.670
You will wait
for the water drop.

401
00:18:29.770 --> 00:18:31.110
That is the call.

402
00:18:33.180 --> 00:18:34.810
We stand by. Ringo's dead.

403
00:18:36.540 --> 00:18:37.550
Copy. D.C.

404
00:18:37.610 --> 00:18:39.110
Mm-mmm.
I don't want to hear it.

405
00:18:39.250 --> 00:18:41.750
I'm gonna get
the choppers airborne.

406
00:18:43.920 --> 00:18:47.490
Firefighter Leone. this is I.C.
Wait for the water drop.

407
00:18:49.290 --> 00:18:50.730
But also...

408
00:18:50.790 --> 00:18:53.230
you make sure that deck gun
could be operational.

409
00:18:53.300 --> 00:18:55.160
Over.

410
00:19:05.340 --> 00:19:06.840
- Okay. It's on.
- All right.

411
00:19:06.940 --> 00:19:08.310
You think any of the fuel
will be able

412
00:19:08.410 --> 00:19:09.910
to reach the pump at this angle?

413
00:19:09.980 --> 00:19:12.110
- Only one way to find out.
- I'll hit the pump switch.

414
00:19:12.250 --> 00:19:14.080
you get the panel
and the deck gun.

415
00:19:14.150 --> 00:19:15.750
Copy.

416
00:19:30.270 --> 00:19:33.000
Bode. fuel can't get
to the pump engine.

417
00:19:33.130 --> 00:19:34.740
Oh. come on. come on.

418
00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:36.240
What's happening. Jake?

419
00:19:36.340 --> 00:19:39.170
The deck gun won't work
if fuel can't reach it.

420
00:19:39.270 --> 00:19:41.140
Yes. There it is. All right.

421
00:19:41.240 --> 00:19:43.040
Okay.
B. we're good.

422
00:19:45.580 --> 00:19:48.280
Cap. Can't get
to the pump panel.

423
00:19:48.380 --> 00:19:49.350
It's too tight to fit.

424
00:19:49.480 --> 00:19:50.820
Let me try.

425
00:19:50.950 --> 00:19:52.420
Come on. I can fit. Easy.

426
00:19:52.490 --> 00:19:54.290
- You don't know how to operate it.
- Yeah.

427
00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:56.190
Yeah. you open the tank
to the pump valve

428
00:19:56.290 --> 00:19:58.590
and. uh. discharge the deck gun.

429
00:19:58.690 --> 00:20:00.330
I spent a lot of time
at the station.

430
00:20:00.430 --> 00:20:02.160
I was paying attention.

431
00:20:02.260 --> 00:20:04.770
Hey. What's going on?
Clock's ticking.

432
00:20:04.830 --> 00:20:06.730
Yeah. he's not gonna fit.
and neither are you.

433
00:20:06.830 --> 00:20:08.500
Look. let me do it.
I-I can do it.

434
00:20:08.640 --> 00:20:10.100
We're running out of time.

435
00:20:11.640 --> 00:20:13.540
I'll get Malcolm
and Ringo ready.

436
00:20:13.640 --> 00:20:15.980
All right. let's go. Come on.

437
00:20:19.710 --> 00:20:21.950
Bode? I'm really sorry.

438
00:20:22.020 --> 00:20:24.050
I shouldn't have ran off
with all those batteries.

439
00:20:24.190 --> 00:20:26.790
You were just trying to be
the kid who did the right thing.

440
00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:29.590
Now be the kid that goes
and gets us to 80 psi.

441
00:20:44.540 --> 00:20:47.740
Tyler. hurry. Tree's cracking.

442
00:20:55.920 --> 00:20:57.450
Come on. Tyler.

443
00:20:57.550 --> 00:20:59.250
Truck's unstable.

444
00:21:12.530 --> 00:21:14.170
Okay. 80.

445
00:21:14.270 --> 00:21:15.240
It's 80 psi.

446
00:21:15.370 --> 00:21:16.800
Done.

447
00:21:16.900 --> 00:21:19.270
- All right. good.
- Now get the hell out of there.

448
00:21:22.440 --> 00:21:24.210
Good job. kid.

449
00:21:24.280 --> 00:21:26.650
All right. let's get
the hose ready. Come on.

450
00:21:28.020 --> 00:21:30.180
- All right. how is he doing?
- Pulse is rapid.

451
00:21:30.250 --> 00:21:31.490
All right.

452
00:21:31.590 --> 00:21:34.520
Okay. he took a bad hit
to the hip.

453
00:21:35.920 --> 00:21:37.660
There's a lot
of pelvic instability.

454
00:21:37.760 --> 00:21:39.260
Probably a fracture.

455
00:21:40.260 --> 00:21:42.130
An artery must be cut.

456
00:21:42.230 --> 00:21:44.300
- What do we do?
- All right.

457
00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:46.430
get him
into a pelvic binder ASAP.

458
00:21:46.530 --> 00:21:49.470
Hey. Grab that blanket
over there.

459
00:21:56.110 --> 00:21:57.480
All right.

460
00:21:59.410 --> 00:22:01.620
Okay. yeah. fold it.
then you're gonna feed it to me

461
00:22:01.750 --> 00:22:03.390
under his legs.

462
00:22:03.450 --> 00:22:05.790
Seesaw it back and forth
up to his hip.

463
00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:08.490
Okay. Let me see it.

464
00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:15.500
All right.

465
00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.330
There you go.

466
00:22:20.440 --> 00:22:21.840
This should stem
the internal bleeding

467
00:22:21.970 --> 00:22:23.170
and stabilize his pelvis.

468
00:22:23.300 --> 00:22:25.070
How do you know this?

469
00:22:25.140 --> 00:22:27.410
I didn't learn it
at the academy.

470
00:22:27.510 --> 00:22:28.810
No. it wasn't the academy.

471
00:22:28.910 --> 00:22:31.710
I learned it from our dad.

472
00:22:32.550 --> 00:22:34.950
He had a similar injury
back in his naval days.

473
00:22:35.050 --> 00:22:39.520
The medic had to fix him up
on the battle mission.

474
00:22:40.320 --> 00:22:41.590
For real?

475
00:22:41.660 --> 00:22:43.690
You know. every time
he would see me

476
00:22:43.830 --> 00:22:46.290
with a twist-tie
at the grocery store.

477
00:22:46.360 --> 00:22:47.630
he would take it

478
00:22:47.730 --> 00:22:51.030
and wrap it around his finger
and twist.

479
00:22:52.500 --> 00:22:55.170
Reminding me how that medic
saved his life.

480
00:22:58.170 --> 00:23:01.040
I need that water drop
on the northwest flank.

481
00:23:01.140 --> 00:23:03.040
No. I don't have 20 minutes.

482
00:23:03.180 --> 00:23:04.680
Find the visibility.

483
00:23:04.810 --> 00:23:06.380
B.C. Perez. this is Crawford.

484
00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:08.020
The deck gun is operational.

485
00:23:08.150 --> 00:23:10.590
Permission to move forward
with self-extrication.

486
00:23:10.690 --> 00:23:12.620
Did I just hear that right?

487
00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:17.060
I told him
to explore the deck gun option.

488
00:23:17.190 --> 00:23:18.530
just as a backup plan.

489
00:23:18.660 --> 00:23:20.030
So you just gave that order?

490
00:23:20.130 --> 00:23:22.400
I did. in case the water drops
were a no-go.

491
00:23:22.500 --> 00:23:24.730
And right now. it's looking
pretty damn smart to me. Chief.

492
00:23:24.870 --> 00:23:26.970
Bode and Jake can egress
with one blast of that deck gun.

493
00:23:27.070 --> 00:23:28.800
You are gambling
with people's lives.

494
00:23:28.900 --> 00:23:31.240
- I don't like these odds.
- Sharon. don't get ugly with me.

495
00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:32.470
I'm-I'm not gambling here.

496
00:23:32.570 --> 00:23:33.940
I'm trying
to give us some options.

497
00:23:35.380 --> 00:23:36.710
Chief. look me in the eyes.

498
00:23:36.780 --> 00:23:38.350
Tell me you wouldn't
make the exact same call

499
00:23:38.410 --> 00:23:40.250
if it wasn't Bode and Jake
out there.

500
00:23:41.080 --> 00:23:42.280
That's really low.

501
00:23:42.380 --> 00:23:43.720
How is that low. Chief. huh?

502
00:23:43.790 --> 00:23:45.150
We want the exact
same thing here.

503
00:23:45.250 --> 00:23:48.790
Captain Crawford.
this is D.C. Leone.

504
00:23:50.120 --> 00:23:53.260
Move forward
with the self-extrication.

505
00:23:56.200 --> 00:23:57.770
Nice work
with the deck gun. Tyler.

506
00:23:57.900 --> 00:23:59.230
Now let's get out of here.

507
00:23:59.300 --> 00:24:01.040
Hey. someone get the other end.

508
00:24:01.100 --> 00:24:02.800
Bode. that's you.
You're...

509
00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.870
- What about the deck gun?
- Yeah. I'll work it.

510
00:24:04.970 --> 00:24:06.270
That way
you can keep eyes on Tyler

511
00:24:06.410 --> 00:24:08.010
when you sprint out of here.
Stay with him.

512
00:24:08.110 --> 00:24:11.180
Let me get your radio
so I can keep Manny filled in.

513
00:24:28.630 --> 00:24:30.060
Right behind you. bro.

514
00:24:30.160 --> 00:24:32.500
You better be.

515
00:24:33.330 --> 00:24:35.800
Ready. Go. go!

516
00:24:44.450 --> 00:24:46.850
Hey. Bode. we don't have eyes
on any of you.

517
00:24:46.950 --> 00:24:49.550
Where are you? Bode.

518
00:24:51.550 --> 00:24:53.020
There. There. there.

519
00:24:53.120 --> 00:24:54.520
Come on. come on. let's go.

520
00:24:54.620 --> 00:24:57.830
Tyler! Oh. my God.

521
00:24:57.930 --> 00:24:59.930
Mom!

522
00:25:00.030 --> 00:25:02.500
Oh. my God.

523
00:25:07.170 --> 00:25:08.900
The gamble almost worked.

524
00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:11.440
It wasn't a gamble.
And it did work.

525
00:25:11.540 --> 00:25:14.110
- Mm. except...
- Except what?

526
00:25:15.180 --> 00:25:18.810
We had... complications.

527
00:25:30.060 --> 00:25:32.830
Aah!

528
00:25:34.630 --> 00:25:37.670
Hey. where's Jake?
Bode. Bode. where's Jake?

529
00:25:40.200 --> 00:25:41.470
Hey. Crawford. I.C.

530
00:25:41.570 --> 00:25:43.570
Status check.
Jake. come in.

531
00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.610
Jake. come in!

532
00:25:52.750 --> 00:25:54.120
I think we can both agree
there's one person to blame

533
00:25:54.180 --> 00:25:56.150
- for this mess.
- I think it's easy to say

534
00:25:56.250 --> 00:25:58.150
something like that
sitting here.

535
00:25:58.250 --> 00:26:00.920
behind your imposing desk.

536
00:26:00.990 --> 00:26:03.690
with your shiny new title.

537
00:26:05.160 --> 00:26:07.030
Battalion Chief Perez
has been courting a war

538
00:26:07.160 --> 00:26:09.260
between himself and fire
for months now.

539
00:26:09.360 --> 00:26:12.570
and with the County Line Fire.
he finally got one.

540
00:26:12.670 --> 00:26:14.940
Conditions created
the perfect storm.

541
00:26:15.040 --> 00:26:16.500
That's not Manny's fault.

542
00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:19.340
Yeah. but why do I get
the impression he enjoyed it?

543
00:26:19.470 --> 00:26:21.680
From someone who was in the dirt
with him. I can tell you

544
00:26:21.780 --> 00:26:24.680
that every decision he made
was excruciating.

545
00:26:24.780 --> 00:26:27.720
Like prematurely working
a very green Three Rock.

546
00:26:27.850 --> 00:26:30.420
Whiplashing engine resources
from the fire line

547
00:26:30.520 --> 00:26:31.990
to that crashed rig.

548
00:26:32.090 --> 00:26:34.890
Allowing Jake and Bode
and that fire crew

549
00:26:34.990 --> 00:26:37.060
to self-rescue... the...
You know. these were all

550
00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:38.830
- Manny's decision. okay?
- No.

551
00:26:38.890 --> 00:26:41.260
Not the last one.
The last one was my call.

552
00:26:41.360 --> 00:26:42.700
as his supervisor.

553
00:26:42.830 --> 00:26:44.200
So. you're what...
you're covering for him now?

554
00:26:44.300 --> 00:26:46.630
This is not
an after-action review.

555
00:26:46.730 --> 00:26:48.900
this is a witch hunt.
Uh. w...

556
00:26:49.040 --> 00:26:52.240
You want to bury Manny.
Sacramento wants to bury Manny.

557
00:26:52.370 --> 00:26:55.080
and you want to use me
as his supervisor

558
00:26:55.210 --> 00:26:56.580
as part of that? Why?

559
00:26:56.710 --> 00:26:59.410
- For-for PR. for Legal?
- Okay. Sharon. I would

560
00:26:59.550 --> 00:27:02.550
tread lightly here
if I were you. okay?

561
00:27:03.950 --> 00:27:06.520
If Perez doesn't go down
for this thing...

562
00:27:06.620 --> 00:27:08.120
someone else might.

563
00:27:12.030 --> 00:27:13.560
The deck gun should've...

564
00:27:13.660 --> 00:27:15.500
- We got to go back in there.
- Can we even get hoses in there?

565
00:27:15.600 --> 00:27:17.770
A water drop is gonna
be better than a hose lay.

566
00:27:17.870 --> 00:27:19.830
The boulders between Jake and us

567
00:27:19.900 --> 00:27:21.700
are too dangerous to cross.
The only thing now

568
00:27:21.770 --> 00:27:23.540
- is to wait for the water drop.
- What? No. no. no.

569
00:27:23.640 --> 00:27:25.070
That water drop
was supposed to be here

570
00:27:25.170 --> 00:27:26.710
- ten minutes ago.
- The winds are gonna change.

571
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:28.780
- We wait for the water.
- W-What do you want to do?

572
00:27:28.910 --> 00:27:30.610
You want to leave Jake out there
with the fire encroaching?

573
00:27:30.750 --> 00:27:32.280
That-That's... that's your plan?

574
00:27:32.380 --> 00:27:34.750
We are in this mess because
of your aggressive approach.

575
00:27:34.850 --> 00:27:36.650
It's now up to me to fix it.

576
00:27:36.750 --> 00:27:38.090
Captain Crawford.

577
00:27:38.190 --> 00:27:40.390
Now that the deck gun
is out of juice.

578
00:27:40.450 --> 00:27:42.220
our only option
is to wait for the water.

579
00:27:42.290 --> 00:27:45.230
No. It's not.
We-we can get in there.

580
00:27:45.290 --> 00:27:46.090
Can you?

581
00:27:46.190 --> 00:27:47.930
D.C.. this is Crawford.

582
00:27:48.060 --> 00:27:51.930
I will find shelter.
Do not send anybody in after me.

583
00:27:52.030 --> 00:27:54.540
But you...
you can't listen to him.

584
00:27:54.600 --> 00:27:57.370
Chief.
It's Jake out there.

585
00:27:57.440 --> 00:27:58.810
Copy. Crawford.

586
00:28:00.240 --> 00:28:01.310
Aw. come on. Chief.

587
00:28:01.410 --> 00:28:03.880
Airbase. this is D.C. Leone.

588
00:28:03.950 --> 00:28:07.480
I have a captain isolated.
surrounded by a wall of fire.

589
00:28:07.580 --> 00:28:08.920
Where is my air support?

590
00:28:15.090 --> 00:28:16.390
That's the call?

591
00:28:16.490 --> 00:28:18.160
Wait for a water drop.
hope for the best?

592
00:28:18.260 --> 00:28:20.130
Hell no.
I'm not leaving Jake in there.

593
00:28:20.230 --> 00:28:22.430
Chief. Jake's the only reason
we got out of there

594
00:28:22.530 --> 00:28:24.600
- in the first place.
- We all know there's another way.

595
00:28:24.670 --> 00:28:27.570
Option one. From earlier.
Come on. Manny.

596
00:28:27.630 --> 00:28:29.800
It's doable now. without
a patient and spineboard.

597
00:28:29.900 --> 00:28:31.940
Let us go through
the steep terrain.

598
00:28:32.040 --> 00:28:34.840
- Sharon'll have my scalp.
- She can have mine. too.

599
00:28:38.810 --> 00:28:40.080
Radios off.

600
00:28:40.150 --> 00:28:42.420
You run point on this.
You're in and you're out.

601
00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:45.650
Safe and fast.
You hear me?

602
00:28:45.750 --> 00:28:47.420
- Get him out. Get him out.
- Yes.

603
00:28:51.990 --> 00:28:56.300
Hey. stop...
Hey. hey! Stop digging!

604
00:28:57.730 --> 00:29:00.840
We're out of time. y'all.
The fire's here.

605
00:29:00.940 --> 00:29:04.570
You have done enough work
for two bulldozers.

606
00:29:04.670 --> 00:29:06.140
Hey. take that in.

607
00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:09.080
You have removed
all flammable vegetation

608
00:29:09.180 --> 00:29:11.050
to prevent
the spread of this fire.

609
00:29:11.180 --> 00:29:13.180
Now what do we do. Cap?

610
00:29:14.150 --> 00:29:15.620
We see if it holds.

611
00:29:15.720 --> 00:29:17.550
Of course it's gonna hold.

612
00:29:18.520 --> 00:29:20.090
Isn't it?

613
00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:51.450
One wrong move.

614
00:29:51.550 --> 00:29:53.490
we take ourselves
out of commission.

615
00:29:53.550 --> 00:29:55.290
make this whole thing worse.

616
00:29:55.390 --> 00:29:57.260
Better get it right. then.

617
00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:12.710
Jake.
We're getting close.

618
00:30:17.040 --> 00:30:18.410
- We got you. bro.
- No.

619
00:30:18.550 --> 00:30:20.550
No. I told you not to come.

620
00:30:20.610 --> 00:30:22.450
- Yeah. we didn't listen.
- The weight of the truck

621
00:30:22.580 --> 00:30:23.890
is pressing on these ladders.

622
00:30:23.950 --> 00:30:25.290
holding down my ankle.

623
00:30:25.390 --> 00:30:26.890
On one. two. three.

624
00:30:38.300 --> 00:30:40.870
Okay. Come on.

625
00:30:40.970 --> 00:30:42.800
Come on. Come on.

626
00:30:48.140 --> 00:30:49.910
Winds steadying.

627
00:30:50.010 --> 00:30:51.880
I.C.. Crew 4.

628
00:30:51.980 --> 00:30:55.320
Three firefighters spotted
leaving the engine crash site.

629
00:30:55.420 --> 00:30:56.750
Crew 4. D.C. Leone.

630
00:30:56.820 --> 00:30:59.290
Confirm status
on the three firefighters.

631
00:30:59.390 --> 00:31:01.760
Negative. Chief.
They're out of zone now.

632
00:31:01.820 --> 00:31:03.260
D.C.. Lookout 2.

633
00:31:03.360 --> 00:31:05.060
I got eyes on 'em.
Heading northwest

634
00:31:05.160 --> 00:31:06.830
through extreme terrain.

635
00:31:07.900 --> 00:31:10.830
Manny? Manny.

636
00:31:10.970 --> 00:31:12.430
How could you do this?

637
00:31:12.530 --> 00:31:14.340
You sent two guys

638
00:31:14.470 --> 00:31:16.140
back into a raging fire.

639
00:31:16.240 --> 00:31:17.170
Off radio.

640
00:31:17.300 --> 00:31:19.610
Against your D.C.'s wishes.

641
00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:21.110
Now that we know
what was lost in this fire.

642
00:31:21.180 --> 00:31:22.240
was it worth the gamble?

643
00:31:22.340 --> 00:31:24.580
Gamble.
There's that word again.

644
00:31:24.680 --> 00:31:26.610
I know your choice of words
is just...

645
00:31:26.710 --> 00:31:28.720
it-it's pure coincidence. right?

646
00:31:29.650 --> 00:31:30.750
Manny. it's not.

647
00:31:30.820 --> 00:31:32.220
Because the way
this report reads.

648
00:31:32.320 --> 00:31:34.020
you were tossing firefighters
back in there

649
00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:35.860
like dice on a craps table.

650
00:31:37.090 --> 00:31:39.330
Blackjack was my game. actually.

651
00:31:40.290 --> 00:31:42.230
And that's all behind me now.

652
00:31:43.000 --> 00:31:45.130
But you want to throw around
some history?

653
00:31:45.200 --> 00:31:48.470
Yours is what...
chasing titles. right?

654
00:31:48.570 --> 00:31:50.500
Yeah.
I'm proud of it.

655
00:31:50.600 --> 00:31:53.370
Can you honestly sit there and
tell me that pinning this on me

656
00:31:53.470 --> 00:31:56.010
isn't in part to make sure
that the higher-ups

657
00:31:56.110 --> 00:31:58.850
know that you're doing right
by your newest title...

658
00:32:00.510 --> 00:32:02.380
Chief?

659
00:32:03.820 --> 00:32:05.550
Yeah. that's what I thought.

660
00:32:08.690 --> 00:32:11.030
All right. easy. easy.

661
00:32:11.130 --> 00:32:12.890
Careful.

662
00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:15.500
- You good?
- Yep.

663
00:32:15.600 --> 00:32:17.730
Easy. Ready?

664
00:32:17.830 --> 00:32:19.630
Here you go.

665
00:32:19.700 --> 00:32:21.370
Come on.

666
00:32:21.470 --> 00:32:23.240
Almost there.

667
00:32:28.210 --> 00:32:30.010
Oh!

668
00:32:33.210 --> 00:32:34.420
Malcolm!

669
00:32:37.020 --> 00:32:38.790
Malcolm!

670
00:32:45.330 --> 00:32:48.000
Hey. Malcolm.

671
00:32:48.860 --> 00:32:49.760
Hey. Malcolm. Hey.

672
00:32:49.900 --> 00:32:51.270
Can you hear us?

673
00:32:53.100 --> 00:32:54.940
Malcolm. come on. man.

674
00:32:55.070 --> 00:32:58.210
Oh. bell got rung.
I'll be good.

675
00:32:58.310 --> 00:33:00.370
No. Hey. hey.

676
00:33:00.440 --> 00:33:01.540
Don't even think about moving.

677
00:33:01.610 --> 00:33:03.640
Oh. I c-I can't...

678
00:33:06.110 --> 00:33:07.650
I can't...

679
00:33:07.750 --> 00:33:09.820
can't get myself out of here.

680
00:33:09.920 --> 00:33:12.150
That's okay.
That's okay.

681
00:33:12.290 --> 00:33:14.120
'cause I'll carry you
out of here. all right?

682
00:33:14.220 --> 00:33:16.260
Kinda tragic.

683
00:33:16.360 --> 00:33:18.790
We... we finally meet.

684
00:33:18.930 --> 00:33:21.260
and all we do
is try to die on each other.

685
00:33:22.300 --> 00:33:24.470
Nah. there's nothing tragic
about that. man.

686
00:33:24.570 --> 00:33:26.530
There's nothing tragic.

687
00:33:26.630 --> 00:33:28.800
- 'Cause you're not dying on me.
- You're not s...

688
00:33:28.940 --> 00:33:32.210
supposed to say that
to a patient.

689
00:33:32.310 --> 00:33:34.540
Listen. you're not a patient.

690
00:33:36.140 --> 00:33:37.840
You're my brother.

691
00:33:39.650 --> 00:33:41.320
You're my brother. okay?

692
00:33:41.450 --> 00:33:44.020
So we're gonna
get you out of here.

693
00:33:44.150 --> 00:33:46.320
Malcolm. Hey. Malcolm.

694
00:33:46.420 --> 00:33:47.690
Malcolm.

695
00:33:47.820 --> 00:33:49.460
B. we got to get out of here.

696
00:33:49.560 --> 00:33:51.690
We're see this through Jake.
Come on. Let's go.

697
00:33:51.830 --> 00:33:53.190
I got him.

698
00:33:53.290 --> 00:33:54.360
Just help me get him up.

699
00:33:54.500 --> 00:33:55.860
Come on. man.

700
00:33:56.830 --> 00:33:59.700
Arms.
One. two. three. go.

701
00:33:59.830 --> 00:34:02.100
All the way. All the way.
There you go.

702
00:34:02.200 --> 00:34:04.170
- I got him.
- Okay.

703
00:34:04.270 --> 00:34:06.710
- I got his bag.
- Yeah.

704
00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:09.010
All right. Three Rock.

705
00:34:09.110 --> 00:34:10.840
Look. I want
to show you something.

706
00:34:10.980 --> 00:34:13.050
Drop your tools.

707
00:34:13.150 --> 00:34:15.820
Over here.
You see all this?

708
00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:17.550
See how it's all gone?

709
00:34:17.650 --> 00:34:19.620
That's a hell of a lot
of black. Cap.

710
00:34:19.690 --> 00:34:22.460
Hey. y'all.
this is what's at stake

711
00:34:22.520 --> 00:34:24.290
every time we go on a call.

712
00:34:24.390 --> 00:34:26.230
All right. now turn around.
gentlemen.

713
00:34:27.930 --> 00:34:30.260
And look at all that
you have protected.

714
00:34:35.700 --> 00:34:37.700
Not too shabby for the new guys.

715
00:34:38.400 --> 00:34:41.410
Well. I don't
know if you're new guys anymore.

716
00:34:41.510 --> 00:34:43.580
You might be my guys.

717
00:34:46.110 --> 00:34:48.050
Hey.
Get back to work.

718
00:35:04.700 --> 00:35:06.970
Medics!
We need support over here!

719
00:35:11.770 --> 00:35:14.610
- What happened?
- He took a hard fall.

720
00:35:15.410 --> 00:35:17.940
Trauma to the head. and he's
been unconscious for a while.

721
00:35:19.610 --> 00:35:21.580
Hey. they're gonna
take good care of him.

722
00:35:21.680 --> 00:35:24.320
Easy for you to say.
Your guys are still vertical.

723
00:35:24.420 --> 00:35:27.150
They're going home tonight.
Mine. not so much.

724
00:35:27.250 --> 00:35:29.390
Hey. let's get that ankle
checked out.

725
00:35:29.490 --> 00:35:30.920
I'll help you...

726
00:35:31.690 --> 00:35:34.830
I told you not to rescue me.

727
00:35:38.100 --> 00:35:41.440
How did you feel. going behind
your commanding officer's back?

728
00:35:41.540 --> 00:35:44.040
I asked for forgiveness.
not permission.

729
00:35:44.140 --> 00:35:47.540
And did you get that
from D.C. Leone... forgiveness?

730
00:35:47.640 --> 00:35:49.080
After the fact?

731
00:35:49.180 --> 00:35:53.980
At. uh. precisely 8:49 p.m.
that night?

732
00:36:17.500 --> 00:36:19.610
You sent them back in

733
00:36:19.710 --> 00:36:22.010
after I told you not to?!

734
00:36:22.110 --> 00:36:23.310
You hit me?

735
00:36:23.410 --> 00:36:24.610
I was wondering how Manny

736
00:36:24.710 --> 00:36:25.850
got that shiner.

737
00:36:25.980 --> 00:36:27.550
It was me.

738
00:36:28.480 --> 00:36:29.980
Yeah. but why?

739
00:36:30.080 --> 00:36:32.420
What's the difference why?

740
00:36:32.490 --> 00:36:34.760
I think context is important.

741
00:36:34.860 --> 00:36:36.590
I lost my objectivity.

742
00:36:36.660 --> 00:36:38.760
Zabel Ridge Fire
came screaming back.

743
00:36:38.860 --> 00:36:41.530
with a family member's life
hanging in the balance

744
00:36:41.660 --> 00:36:43.460
in an impossible fire.

745
00:36:43.530 --> 00:36:45.500
'Cause Manny lied to you?

746
00:36:45.630 --> 00:36:47.730
He lied to me
'cause I needed to be lied to.

747
00:36:47.830 --> 00:36:51.040
He was the only leader there
who was still able

748
00:36:51.170 --> 00:36:53.840
to assess the risk
of going through the boulders.

749
00:36:53.940 --> 00:36:55.780
If it wasn't for him.

750
00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:59.050
we would have lost
a firefighter out there.

751
00:37:01.480 --> 00:37:04.050
What about Jake's brother?

752
00:37:04.180 --> 00:37:05.990
Well. I... You know...

753
00:37:06.090 --> 00:37:08.360
Firefighters get hurt.

754
00:37:08.460 --> 00:37:09.890
they take risks.

755
00:37:10.020 --> 00:37:12.960
And I'm convinced
that your call. Manny.

756
00:37:13.030 --> 00:37:14.700
to send him and Bode in there

757
00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:17.100
is the only reason
that Jake is alive today.

758
00:37:19.530 --> 00:37:21.130
And besides. I...

759
00:37:21.200 --> 00:37:24.940
I got some good advice about
how to do these hot washes.

760
00:37:25.770 --> 00:37:27.640
Which was?

761
00:37:27.710 --> 00:37:29.580
Put yourself in their shoes.

762
00:37:30.510 --> 00:37:33.580
Would you make the calls
in good faith?

763
00:37:35.480 --> 00:37:37.580
Anyhow. you both can go.

764
00:37:37.720 --> 00:37:40.890
You'll be getting a copy of this
report within a week or so.

765
00:37:40.990 --> 00:37:42.660
Really? That's it?

766
00:37:42.760 --> 00:37:45.090
Doesn't Sacramento
need a head to roll?

767
00:37:45.230 --> 00:37:47.930
Let it be mine.
I can handle Sacramento.

768
00:37:48.030 --> 00:37:50.200
It's what
I'm really good at. anyway.

769
00:37:50.260 --> 00:37:52.800
It's that shiny
new job title and all.

770
00:37:55.640 --> 00:37:57.570
Kill me now.

771
00:38:13.390 --> 00:38:15.960
I don't know if you can
hear me. Malcolm.

772
00:38:16.820 --> 00:38:17.960
But you made
quite the impression

773
00:38:18.090 --> 00:38:20.290
on all of us over at 42.

774
00:38:22.030 --> 00:38:24.100
Particularly your brother.

775
00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:28.170
Who's not too happy
with me right now.

776
00:38:30.740 --> 00:38:32.740
Oh. man.

777
00:38:36.980 --> 00:38:39.580
I need you to know that

778
00:38:39.650 --> 00:38:42.080
I'm sorry I sent you in.

779
00:38:44.050 --> 00:38:45.920
I'm so sorry.

780
00:38:50.890 --> 00:38:53.290
I can't believe that
Tyler agreed to talk to the ATF

781
00:38:53.390 --> 00:38:55.730
about Landon's role
in the Zabel Ridge Fire.

782
00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:57.960
- He was terrified before.
- He lived through a fire

783
00:38:58.060 --> 00:38:59.970
- in a tinfoil shelter. so...
- Mm.

784
00:39:00.070 --> 00:39:02.640
Probably a little less scared
to talk to the feds now.

785
00:39:02.740 --> 00:39:05.510
Uh. you... Don't downplay
your part in it.

786
00:39:06.270 --> 00:39:10.040
Tyler told me that.
because of you.

787
00:39:10.140 --> 00:39:12.250
he wants to be the kid
that helps.

788
00:39:12.310 --> 00:39:15.250
- He was crucial on that fire.
- Yeah.

789
00:39:16.120 --> 00:39:18.150
I owe your chief an apology.

790
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:20.450
I yelled at him.

791
00:39:20.520 --> 00:39:21.820
I threatened his job. too.

792
00:39:21.920 --> 00:39:24.090
And you were all just
keeping Tyler alive.

793
00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:28.830
You're the last thing that
Manny's worried about right now.

794
00:39:32.830 --> 00:39:34.100
You know. after this.

795
00:39:34.200 --> 00:39:37.000
we can start moving on
from-from Landon.

796
00:39:37.100 --> 00:39:38.940
and also from the fire.

797
00:39:39.040 --> 00:39:41.070
I can't wait.

798
00:39:43.010 --> 00:39:44.880
I'm happy for you.

799
00:39:45.010 --> 00:39:48.210
Thank you. Thank you.

800
00:39:49.620 --> 00:39:52.050
You know.
I'd love to buy you dinner.

801
00:39:52.190 --> 00:39:53.890
at some point. maybe.

802
00:39:54.990 --> 00:39:56.420
As a-as a thank-you.

803
00:39:56.520 --> 00:39:58.060
- For...
- Uh...

804
00:39:58.160 --> 00:39:59.730
you know.

805
00:39:59.860 --> 00:40:02.660
Is that too much?
It's too much.

806
00:40:02.760 --> 00:40:04.670
- It's fine.
- No. it. um...

807
00:40:04.730 --> 00:40:08.130
It... I don't want
to make it weird. Ugh...

808
00:40:08.200 --> 00:40:09.840
Is it weird that I asked you?

809
00:40:09.900 --> 00:40:12.240
No. uh. I'd-I'd like that.

810
00:40:12.370 --> 00:40:13.870
- Y... Wait.
- Yeah.

811
00:40:14.010 --> 00:40:15.940
- What the hell is this?
- We've made an initial arrest

812
00:40:16.040 --> 00:40:17.680
of your son. Ms. MacKenzie.

813
00:40:17.780 --> 00:40:19.210
- You can follow us to the station.
- Wait. wait. wait. wait.

814
00:40:19.350 --> 00:40:22.380
- An arrest for what?
- The charge is arson.

815
00:40:22.480 --> 00:40:23.680
For Zabel Ridge.

816
00:40:23.750 --> 00:40:25.720
No.
Y-You've got the wrong guy.

817
00:40:25.820 --> 00:40:27.220
You told me
I could pick the kind of kid

818
00:40:27.350 --> 00:40:29.220
I want to be. Bode. and...

819
00:40:29.320 --> 00:40:31.020
I'm the kid
who does the right thing.

820
00:40:31.090 --> 00:40:32.930
- Tyler. what?
- I'm really sorry. Mom.

821
00:40:33.060 --> 00:40:34.500
- You're serious?
- Come with us. man.

822
00:40:34.560 --> 00:40:35.730
- Tyler.
- You-you can't do this.

823
00:40:35.830 --> 00:40:37.560
Where...
where are you taking him?

824
00:40:37.660 --> 00:40:39.300
Tyler!

824
00:40:40.305 --> 00:41:40.237
Do you want subtitles for any video?
